line_1: And down he sets her, and again unbinds;
line_2: The Miller in their Mirth his Folly finds,

line_1: But now that veil the youth unbinds,
line_2: See! its folds catch the passing winds,

line_1: Each tangled braid with glistening teeth unbinds
line_2: And with the floating treasure musks the winds. —

line_1: Now the glad earth her frozen zone unbinds,
line_2: And o'er her bosom breathe the western winds:

line_1: In early years connected, time unbinds.
